I was crossing newly marked crosswalk and was nearly struck by red Tesla north on Jamieson Avenue at intersection of Courthouse Square. Tesla driver saw me crossing but sped up to cross in front of me in the crosswalk. There are two cameras on Federal courthouse building that likely recorded the incident.

I was riding my bike straight through the intersection on Jamieson Ave toward Old Town.  I had the green light.  A driver in a sedan turning right on red from Mill Rd failed to stop on her red light and turned right and almost ran into the back of my bike.  I'm not even sure how she didn't hit me - it was that close.  The waved an apology after she finally saw me.
